   ### Rule 0.6: Report Files (Disk Only When Explicit or HandsOff)
   - **Default:** Do **NOT** create markdown report files under **`Cursor-Project/reports/`** after routine tasks, Q&A, bug validation, test runs, or general chat. Put the full answer in the chat reply.
   - **When you MUST write a persisted `.md` report file (narrow list):**
     - **Rule 37 (HandsOff):** `{JIRA_KEY}.md` under **HandsOff reports** (path layout below; Slack/orchestrator steps use that file).
     - **Chat reports area:** **Only** when the user runs **`/report`**, or **explicitly** asks to save/export/write a report to disk (same intent in any language). Then use **Chat reports** (or **Feedback/** if the user names that area). No other workflow may require a new report file on disk by default.
   - **Bug validation (Rule 32):** Full analysis and verdict **in chat only** unless the user also runs **`/report`** or explicitly asks to save (e.g. `BugValidation_*.md` under **Chat reports**). Rule 32 does **not** mandate a disk file.
   - **Optional other exports:** If the user explicitly asks for a written run log or “save this to reports”, use editor/file tools — **no** Python `ReportingService` in this workspace
   - **Path layout (when a file is written):** `Cursor-Project/reports/<Chat reports|HandsOff reports|Feedback>/YYYY/<english-month>/<DD>/<filename>.md` — resolve segments per **`Cursor-Project/reports/README.md`** (reuse same-day folders; create missing segments only when writing a file). Example names: `Summary_{HHMM}.md`, `{JIRA_KEY}.md` (HandsOff), `BugValidation_*.md` (only if user requested persistence)
   - **Violation:** Critical only if **Rule 37** file is skipped when HandsOff was run, or if the user ran **`/report`** / explicitly requested a saved file and it was omitted — not when you omit optional on-disk summaries
   
